    "body": "Thanks for reporting this. The crash actually doesn't happen any more on develop:\n\n```\n> eth.getTransactionCount(\"0x52bc44d5378309ee2abf1539bf71de1b7d7be3b5\", 1305086)\nMissing trie node 1055ec6fc3012b17c71893bb8802b0f1e14fad9034e60f4c71407584b8f517cc\n    at web3.js:3119:20\n    at web3.js:6018:15\n    at web3.js:4990:36\n    at <anonymous>:1:1\n```\n\n```\n$ curl -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionCount\",\"params\": [\"0x52bc44d5378309ee2abf1539bf71de1b7d7be3b5\", 1305086], \"id\":1}' -X POST localhost:8545\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"error\":{\"code\":-32000,\"message\":\"Missing trie node 1055ec6fc3012b17c71893bb8802b0f1e14fad9034e60f4c71407584b8f517cc\"}}\n```\n\nJust a side note, a fast synced node (or a pruned one for that matter) will only be able to retrieve state data for the blocks that it still retains historical state (i.e. top 1-2K blocks +-). Hence the missing trie node error: there's simply not enough past data retained to answer this question.\n",
